Senior Business Development Manager Job (Property Development), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Business Development
Industry:
Property & Real Estate
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
06 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is currently recruiting on behalf of a leading multinational company with a core focus on infrastructure and property. As an established developer, our client is diversified across 11 countries in the Asia-Pacific region. The company’s presence in Indonesia spans 15 years, with projects throughout the country, including Jakarta, Surabaya, Yogyakarta, Bintan, Bali, Batam and Manado. As expansion continues, our client is seeking a qualified candidate for the job of Senior Business Development Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia.
Key job responsibilities:
Sourcing for new real estate investments that fit the company’s requirements and assessing new businesses, and analysing business opportunities.
Conducting financial feasibility studies and developing proposals for new business opportunities.
Be accountable for initiatives and programs, duties include negotiating contracts, initiating proposals, and closing deals.
Conducting due diligence of target assets/deals.
Developing periodic market trend data, demand supply dynamic, competitive pricing and product analysis
Prepare investment update reports, investment papers, and other presentations if required
Requirements:
Bachelor’s Degree (or equivalent) in Real Estate, Engineering, Business Administration, Finance  or other related field from reputable university
At least 7 years relevant experience in property, valuation and business development in related field, preferably with developers.
Sound understanding of the real estate market in Indonesia
High proficiency in written and spoken English
Strong analytical skills, excellent in numbers, have high attention to details.
High proficiency in performing financial analysis and projection using Microsoft Excel and Have a complete understanding and application of principles, concepts, and practices.
Excellent time management’s skill and decision making skills
Relies on extensive experience and judgment to plan and accomplish the goals.
Proven planning and organizational skills including administration.
Good interpersonal & negotiation skills
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.